      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Harold Blake Walker (d. 2002) was an American Presbyterian clergyman and author.  He was was the senior pastor of the First Presbyterian Church of Evanston, Illinois for many years, and his column, "Living Faith," appeared in the Chicago Tribune and other newspapers from 1954 to 1975.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Harold Blake Walker Papers</emph> contains manuscripts, memorabilia and published books.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
